# TradeLedger Auth API Documentation

Base URL: `http://localhost:5000`  
Auth Base Path: `/auth`  
Content-Type: `application/json` (except SSR verify route)

---

## 1) Register

### Endpoint
`POST /auth/register`

### Description
Creates a new user account, stores hashed password + public key, sends verification email.

### Request JSON
```json
{
  "business_name": "Acme Traders",
  "email": "owner@acme.com",
  "password": "StrongPass@123",
  "phone": "+919999999999"
}
```

### Response JSON Outcomes

**201 Created**
```json
{
  "message": "Registration successful. Please verify your email."
}
```

**400 Bad Request** (missing required fields)
```json
{
  "message": "business_name, email, password and phone are required"
}
```

**409 Conflict** (email already exists)
```json
{
  "message": "User already exists"
}
```

**500 Internal Server Error** (unexpected server/DB/email failure)
```json
{
  "message": "Internal server error"
}
```

---

## 2) Verify Email (SSR)

### Endpoint
`GET /auth/verify-email?token=<RAW_TOKEN>`

### Description
Verifies email using token from email link. Returns HTML page (SSR), not JSON.

### Request
No JSON body. Token is query param.

### HTML Outcomes

**200 OK**
- Page title: `Email Verified Successfully`
- Message: `Your email has been verified. You can now log in.`

**400 Bad Request** (missing token)
- Page title: `Invalid or expired link`
- Message: `Verification token is missing.`

**400 Bad Request** (invalid/expired token)
- Page title: `Invalid or expired link`
- Message: `Invalid or expired link`

**500 Internal Server Error**
- Page from global error handling (JSON if thrown to middleware)

---

## 3) Login

### Endpoint
`POST /auth/login`

### Description
Authenticates verified user and returns JWT token.

### Request JSON
```json
{
  "email": "owner@acme.com",
  "password": "StrongPass@123"
}
```

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "token": "<JWT_TOKEN>"
}
```

**400 Bad Request** (missing email/password)
```json
{
  "message": "Email and password are required"
}
```

**401 Unauthorized** (invalid email or password)
```json
{
  "message": "Invalid credentials"
}
```

**403 Forbidden** (email not verified)
```json
{
  "message": "Please verify your email before logging in"
}
```

**500 Internal Server Error**
```json
{
  "message": "Internal server error"
}
```

---

## 4) Forgot Password

### Endpoint
`POST /auth/forgot-password`

### Description
Generates reset token, stores hashed token + expiry (15 min), sends reset email if user exists.

### Request JSON
```json
{
  "email": "owner@acme.com"
}
```

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK** (always generic to avoid user enumeration)
```json
{
  "message": "If the email exists, a reset link has been sent."
}
```

**400 Bad Request** (missing email)
```json
{
  "message": "Email is required"
}
```

**500 Internal Server Error**
```json
{
  "message": "Internal server error"
}
```

---

## 5) Reset Password

### Endpoint
`POST /auth/reset-password`

### Description
Resets password using valid reset token and updates `password_updated_at`.

### Request JSON
```json
{
  "token": "<RAW_RESET_TOKEN>",
  "new_password": "NewStrongPass@456"
}
```

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "message": "Password has been reset successfully"
}
```

**400 Bad Request** (missing token/new_password)
```json
{
  "message": "token and new_password are required"
}
```

**400 Bad Request** (invalid or expired token)
```json
{
  "message": "Invalid or expired reset token"
}
```

**500 Internal Server Error**
```json
{
  "message": "Internal server error"
}
```

---

## 6) Get Key Seed (Protected)

### Endpoint
`POST /auth/get-key-seed`

### Description
Returns seed values (`created_at`, `password_updated_at`) after JWT + password check.  
Private key is never returned.

### Required Header
`Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>`

### Request JSON
```json
{
  "password": "StrongPass@123"
}
```

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "created_at": "2026-04-30T16:00:00.000Z",
  "password_updated_at": "2026-04-30T16:00:00.000Z"
}
```

**400 Bad Request** (missing password)
```json
{
  "message": "Password is required"
}
```

**401 Unauthorized** (missing/invalid JWT)
```json
{
  "message": "Unauthorized"
}
```
or
```json
{
  "message": "Invalid or expired token"
}
```

**401 Unauthorized** (wrong password)
```json
{
  "message": "Invalid credentials"
}
```

**404 Not Found** (user not found for token userId)
```json
{
  "message": "User not found"
}
```

**500 Internal Server Error**
```json
{
  "message": "Internal server error"
}
```

---

## Global / App-Level Routes

### Health Check
`GET /`

**200 OK** (text response)
```text
API running
```

### Unknown Routes
Any non-existing route returns:

**404 Not Found**
```json
{
  "message": "Route not found"
}
```

---

## Security Notes

- Passwords are hashed using bcrypt.
- Email/reset tokens are hashed before DB storage.
- Token comparisons use timing-safe checks.
- JWT auth is required for protected endpoint(s).
- Email must be verified before login.
- Private key is deterministic and never stored/returned.
- SMTP credentials come from `.env` only.

---

# User Module API Documentation

User Base Path: `/v1/api/users`  
Requires Header: `Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>` for all endpoints below.

## 1) Get My Profile

### Endpoint
`GET /v1/api/users/me`

### Description
Returns full profile for logged-in user. Does not expose `password_hash` or private key.

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "id": 1,
  "business_name": "ABC Traders",
  "email": "abc@gmail.com",
  "phone_primary": "9999999999",
  "public_key": "PUBLIC_KEY_VALUE",
  "details": {
    "address": "Bangalore",
    "phone": "9999999999",
    "gst_number": "29ABCDE1234F1Z5"
  }
}
```

If no row exists in `user_details`, `details` will be `null`.

**401 Unauthorized**
```json
{
  "message": "Unauthorized"
}
```
or
```json
{
  "message": "Invalid or expired token"
}
```

**404 Not Found**
```json
{
  "message": "User not found"
}
```

---

## 2) Update My Profile

### Endpoint
`PUT /v1/api/users/me`

### Description
Updates `users` table (`business_name`, `phone_primary`) and updates/inserts row in `user_details` (`address`, `gst_number`).

### Request JSON
```json
{
  "business_name": "ABC Traders Pvt Ltd",
  "phone_primary": "9999999999",
  "address": "MG Road, Bangalore",
  "gst_number": "29ABCDE1234F1Z5"
}
```

### Validation
- `business_name` is required and must be non-empty.
- `gst_number` is optional, but if present must be valid GST format.

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "id": 1,
  "business_name": "ABC Traders Pvt Ltd",
  "email": "abc@gmail.com",
  "phone_primary": "9999999999",
  "public_key": "PUBLIC_KEY_VALUE",
  "details": {
    "address": "MG Road, Bangalore",
    "phone": "9999999999",
    "gst_number": "29ABCDE1234F1Z5"
  }
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "message": "business_name is required"
}
```
or
```json
{
  "message": "Invalid gst_number format"
}
```

**404 Not Found**
```json
{
  "message": "User not found"
}
```

---

## 3) Get Public User Profile

### Endpoint
`GET /v1/api/users/:id`

### Description
Returns only public profile fields for B2B discovery.

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "id": 2,
  "business_name": "XYZ Suppliers",
  "public_key": "PUBLIC_KEY_VALUE",
  "gst_number": "27ABCDE1234F1Z9",
  "is_verified": true
}
```

### Not Returned
- `email`
- `phone_primary`
- `password_hash`

**404 Not Found**
```json
{
  "message": "User not found"
}
```

---

## 4) Search Users

### Endpoint
`GET /v1/api/users/search?q=<search_text>`

### Description
Searches by `business_name` or `gst_number` (case-insensitive), limited to 10 results.

### Query Parameter
- `q` (required)

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "count": 2,
  "results": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "business_name": "ABC Traders",
      "gst_number": "29ABCDE1234F1Z5"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "business_name": "ABC Components",
      "gst_number": null
    }
  ]
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "message": "Query parameter q is required"
}
```

---

# Request Module API Documentation

Request Base Path: `/v1/api/requests`  
Requires Header: `Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>` for all endpoints below.

State Flow: `CREATE -> SENT -> SEEN -> REVIEWED -> CONVERTED`

## Common Response Envelope

Successful responses use:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {}
}
```

Error responses use:
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Error reason"
}
```

## 1) Create Request

### Endpoint
`POST /v1/api/requests`

### Request JSON
```json
{
  "receiver_id": 2,
  "request_data": {
    "amount": 35000,
    "note": "Need 30-day credit"
  }
}
```

### Rules
- `sender_id` is always taken from JWT (`req.user.id`)
- `request_id` is generated as UUID
- `receiver_id` must be a number
- `request_data` must be an object

### Response JSON Outcomes

**201 Created**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": 10,
    "request_id": "2f06afce-9226-4140-b15f-d19716ec7804",
    "sender_id": 1,
    "receiver_id": 2,
    "request_data": {
      "amount": 35000,
      "note": "Need 30-day credit"
    },
    "is_reviewed": false,
    "reviewed_at": null,
    "is_converted_to_invoice": false,
    "sent_at": "2026-05-01T11:30:00.000Z",
    "is_seen": false,
    "seen_at": null
  }
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "receiver_id (number) and request_data (object) are required"
}
```

## 2) List Requests (Limited Fields)

### Endpoint
`GET /v1/api/requests?type=sent|received`

### Rules
- `type=sent` returns rows where `sender_id = logged-in user`
- `type=received` returns rows where `receiver_id = logged-in user`
- limited to latest 20 records
- only limited fields returned

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": [
    {
      "request_id": "2f06afce-9226-4140-b15f-d19716ec7804",
      "sender_id": 1,
      "receiver_id": 2,
      "sent_at": "2026-05-01T11:30:00.000Z"
    }
  ]
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "type must be either sent or received"
}
```

## 3) Get Full Request

### Endpoint
`GET /v1/api/requests/:request_id`

### Rules
- only sender or receiver can read a request
- if receiver fetches and `is_seen = false`, system auto-updates:
  - `is_seen = true`
  - `seen_at = NOW()`

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": 10,
    "request_id": "2f06afce-9226-4140-b15f-d19716ec7804",
    "sender_id": 1,
    "receiver_id": 2,
    "request_data": {
      "amount": 35000,
      "note": "Need 30-day credit"
    },
    "is_reviewed": false,
    "reviewed_at": null,
    "is_converted_to_invoice": false,
    "sent_at": "2026-05-01T11:30:00.000Z",
    "is_seen": true,
    "seen_at": "2026-05-01T11:32:05.000Z"
  }
}
```

**403 Forbidden**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Unauthorized to access this request"
}
```

**404 Not Found**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Request not found"
}
```

## 4) Update Request

### Endpoint
`PUT /v1/api/requests/:request_id`

### Request JSON
```json
{
  "receiver_id": 3,
  "request_data": {
    "amount": 50000,
    "note": "Updated quantity"
  }
}
```

### Rules
- only sender can update
- only if `is_seen = false`
- blocked if already converted

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "request_id": "2f06afce-9226-4140-b15f-d19716ec7804",
    "sender_id": 1,
    "receiver_id": 3,
    "request_data": {
      "amount": 50000,
      "note": "Updated quantity"
    }
  }
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Seen request cannot be updated"
}
```
or
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Converted request cannot be modified"
}
```

**403 Forbidden**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Only sender can update this request"
}
```

## 5) Delete Request

### Endpoint
`DELETE /v1/api/requests/:request_id`

### Rules
- only sender can delete
- only if `is_seen = false`
- blocked if already converted

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "request_id": "2f06afce-9226-4140-b15f-d19716ec7804",
    "deleted": true
  }
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Seen request cannot be deleted"
}
```
or
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Converted request cannot be deleted"
}
```

**403 Forbidden**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Only sender can delete this request"
}
```

## 6) Review Request (Accept/Reject)

### Endpoint
`PUT /v1/api/requests/:request_id/review`

### Request JSON
```json
{
  "action": "accept"
}
```
or
```json
{
  "action": "reject"
}
```

### Rules
- only receiver can review
- only if `is_reviewed = false`
- blocked if already converted
- on success:
  - `is_reviewed = true`
  - `reviewed_at = NOW()`
  - `request_data.review_action = action`

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "request_id": "2f06afce-9226-4140-b15f-d19716ec7804",
    "is_reviewed": true,
    "reviewed_at": "2026-05-01T11:40:00.000Z",
    "request_data": {
      "amount": 50000,
      "note": "Updated quantity",
      "review_action": "accept"
    }
  }
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Request already reviewed"
}
```
or
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Converted request cannot be reviewed again"
}
```

**403 Forbidden**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Only receiver can review this request"
}
```

## 7) Convert Request to Invoice

### Endpoint
`PUT /v1/api/requests/:request_id/convert`

### Rules
- request must be reviewed first (`is_reviewed = true`)
- only participants (sender or receiver) can convert
- blocked if already converted
- on success: `is_converted_to_invoice = true`

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "request_id": "2f06afce-9226-4140-b15f-d19716ec7804",
    "is_converted_to_invoice": true
  }
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Request must be reviewed before conversion"
}
```
or
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Request already converted"
}
```

**403 Forbidden**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Unauthorized to convert this request"
}
```

---

# Transaction Module API Documentation

Transaction Base Path: `/v1/api/transactions`  
Requires Header: `Authorization: Bearer <JWT_TOKEN>` for all endpoints below.

State Flow: `CREATED -> SEEN -> ACCEPTED -> ON_BLOCKCHAIN`

## Common Response Envelope

Successful responses use:
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {}
}
```

Error responses generally use:
```json
{
  "message": "Error reason"
}
```
or validation responses use:
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Error reason"
}
```

## 1) Create Transaction

### Endpoint
`POST /v1/api/transactions`

### Request JSON
```json
{
  "receiver_id": 2,
  "invoice_data": {
    "amount": 42000,
    "invoice_number": "A-101",
    "items": [
      { "name": "Steel Rod", "qty": 20, "rate": 2100 }
    ]
  }
}
```

### Rules
- `sender_id` comes from JWT (`req.user.id`)
- `invoice_id` auto-generates as `INV-<timestamp>`
- `receiver_id` must be a number
- `invoice_data` must be an object

### Response JSON Outcomes

**201 Created**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": 1,
    "invoice_id": "INV-1746140000000",
    "sender_id": 1,
    "receiver_id": 2,
    "invoice_data": {
      "amount": 42000,
      "invoice_number": "A-101"
    },
    "is_seen": false,
    "seen_at": null,
    "is_accepted": false,
    "accepted_at": null,
    "is_on_blockchain": false,
    "created_at": "2026-05-01T18:00:00.000Z"
  }
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "receiver_id (number) and invoice_data (object) are required"
}
```

## 2) List Transactions

### Endpoint
`GET /v1/api/transactions?type=sent|received`

### Rules
- `type=sent` returns sender side transactions
- `type=received` returns receiver side transactions

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "invoice_id": "INV-1746140000000",
      "created_at": "2026-05-01T18:00:00.000Z",
      "user_id": 2
    }
  ]
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "type must be either sent or received"
}
```

## 3) Get Full Transaction

### Endpoint
`GET /v1/api/transactions/:id`

### Rules
- only sender or receiver can read
- if receiver reads first time and `is_seen = false`, system auto-updates:
  - `is_seen = true`
  - `seen_at = NOW()`

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": 1,
    "invoice_id": "INV-1746140000000",
    "sender_id": 1,
    "receiver_id": 2,
    "invoice_data": {
      "amount": 42000
    },
    "is_seen": true,
    "seen_at": "2026-05-01T18:05:00.000Z",
    "is_accepted": false,
    "is_on_blockchain": false
  }
}
```

**403 Forbidden**
```json
{
  "message": "Unauthorized"
}
```

**404 Not Found**
```json
{
  "message": "Transaction not found"
}
```

## 4) Update Transaction

### Endpoint
`PUT /v1/api/transactions/:id`

### Request JSON
```json
{
  "invoice_data": {
    "amount": 45000,
    "note": "Updated before viewed"
  }
}
```

### Rules
- only sender can update
- blocked once receiver has seen it (`is_seen = true`)

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "id": 1,
    "invoice_data": {
      "amount": 45000,
      "note": "Updated before viewed"
    }
  }
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "message": "Cannot edit after seen"
}
```

**403 Forbidden**
```json
{
  "message": "Unauthorized"
}
```

## 5) Delete Transaction

### Endpoint
`DELETE /v1/api/transactions/:id`

### Rules
- only sender can delete
- blocked once receiver has seen it (`is_seen = true`)

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Deleted"
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "message": "Cannot delete after seen"
}
```

**403 Forbidden**
```json
{
  "message": "Unauthorized"
}
```

## 6) Accept Transaction (Writes to Blockchain)

### Endpoint
`POST /v1/api/transactions/:id/accept`

### Rules
- only receiver can accept
- cannot accept twice
- done in DB transaction with row lock (`FOR UPDATE`)
- on success:
  - `is_accepted = true`
  - block is inserted in `blockchain`
  - `is_on_blockchain = true`

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Accepted and added to blockchain"
}
```

**400 Bad Request**
```json
{
  "message": "Already accepted"
}
```

**403 Forbidden**
```json
{
  "message": "Unauthorized"
}
```

## 7) Verify Blockchain Integrity

### Endpoint
`POST /v1/api/transactions/:id/verify`

### Rules
- recomputes hash using stored block data + previous hash
- compares with stored `current_hash`

### Response JSON Outcomes

**200 OK (valid)**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "valid": true,
    "stored_hash": "6f2d...d1a0",
    "recalculated_hash": "6f2d...d1a0"
  }
}
```

**200 OK (invalid/tampered)**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "valid": false,
    "stored_hash": "6f2d...d1a0",
    "recalculated_hash": "ab91...7f22"
  }
}
```

**200 OK (no block yet)**
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "valid": false,
    "reason": "No block found"
  }
}
```
